description: modern python standards
alwaysApply: false
---
- Type annotate method signatures always.
- Type annotate variables where clarity is needed.
- Prefer | instead of Optional or Union.
- Code concise, technical, Python that adheres to PEP 8 and PEP 585.
- Code to modern Python standards targeting version 3.10 or later.
- Use absolute import paths.
- When possible, place imports at top of module.
- Sort imports grouped by - standard libraries -> third-party libraries -> local libraries. Within each group, sort alphabetically.
- Use nested context managers only and avoid combining multiple context managers into single statement.